<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>When converting structures to XML it is not really appropriate to have tags automatically created from numeric keys.</p>

<p>For example, consider the following array containing a list of product items:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
array("products" =&gt;
    array(
        array("product" =&gt; array("id" =&gt; 1, "name" =&gt; "Car")),
        array("product" =&gt; array("id" =&gt; 2, "name" =&gt; "Truck"))
    )
)
</code></pre>

<p>The expected XML is:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
1Car2Truck</code></pre>

<p>Zend_Rest_Server constructs:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
1Car2Truck</code></pre>

<p>Zend_Rest_Server should have an option to disable the inclusion of numeric keys as tags (key_0, key_1, key_2...)</p>

    </div>
</div>

